        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 5:18PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Free Union to near Charlottesville to 8
miles north of Centenary. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Lake Monticello around 525 PM EDT.
Troy around 535 PM EDT.
Palmyra and Boswells Tavern around 540 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Dixie, Nahor, Green
Springs, Stage Junction, Zion Crossroads, Central Plains, Antioch,
Union Mills, Caledonia, and Wildwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for central
Virginia.</instruction>
